  "version": 1,
  "description": "Durable catalog taxonomy: three orthogonal axes for classifying every agent. INDUSTRY is who the enterprise is (cross_industry for horizontal shared-services agents). FUNCTION is the business capability the agent serves; horizontal functions map 1:1 to the legacy `department` field, shared functions are capabilities many industries specialize (a retailer's supply chain, a telco's billing), vertical functions are native to one industry (merchandising, claims, network operations). VALUE STREAM is the industry's operating segmentation — each vertical value stream binds to exactly one function, which is how 'a retailer has a special kind of procurement' is expressed: the retail Supply Chain & Fulfillment stream carries function supply_chain, which declares specializes: [procurement]. Deriving an industry flavor of an existing horizontal agent is the other path: `ge okf customize --base <horizontal-id> --id <new-id> --vertical <industry>` produces an OKF variant bundle (variant_kind: vertical) whose lineage the registry tracks.",
